    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/79"
                            >Hugo</persName> divina largiente clemencia <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >rex</rs>. Si sacris ac venerabilibus locis temporalia atque transitoria
                        concedimus, magnam apud Dominum remunerari in futuro nequaquam diffidimus.
                        Quocirca noverit omnium fidelium sanctae Dei Aeclesiae nostrorumque
                        presencium scilicet ac futurorum industria, <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Archbishops" ref="#people/45">Lampertum</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/221">sanctae <placeName ref="#places/147"
                                >Mediolanensis</placeName> ecclesiae</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopum</rs> nec non et <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Bishops" ref="#people/78">Adelbertum</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/189">sanctae <placeName ref="#places/10"
                                >Bergamensis</placeName> sedis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">presulem</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Countess #siblingOf" ref="#people/1517"
                            >Ermengardis</persName> gloriosissimam <rs key="#Countess"
                            >comitissam</rs> karissimamque <rs key="#siblingOf">germanam</rs>
                        nostram et <persName key="#Intercessory #Palatine_count" ref="#people/1518"
                            >Giselbertum</persName> illustrem <rs key="#Palatine_count">comitem
                            palatii</rs> humiliter nostram <rs key="#Intercessory">exorasse</rs>
                        celsitudinem, quatenus ob amore superne remunerationis per nostri precepti
                        paginam quoddam <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> infra <placeName
                            ref="#places/43">civitate Placentina</placeName> a beate videlicet
                        memoriae <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/55">Angelberga</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatrice</rs> constructum et <orgName
                            key="#Houses #Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Castle #Markets #Periodic_markets #Public_exactions #Profits_of_justice #Districtio #Churches #Monasteries #Cells/hermitages #Abbesses #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/53">in honore sancti Sixti</orgName> dedicatum
                            <persName key="#Abbesses" ref="#people/67">Berte</persName>
                        gloriosissime <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatisse</rs> consanguineae nostrae cum
                        omnibus suis pertinenciis confirmare dignaremur, simul quoque roborantes et
                        in perpetuum concedentes eidem monasterio quasdam <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >cortes</rs>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/40"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Vuardestallam</placeName></geogName> scilicet,
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/110"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/141">Campum Miliatio</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/207"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/462">Curtem Novam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/112"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/354">Sexto</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/38"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/32">Luciariam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/77"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/361">Litora Paludiana</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/80"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/362">Villole</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/42"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/34">Piguniariam</placeName></geogName>, cum adiacenciis
                        eorum et omnia quecumque memorata imperatrix institutionis suae paginam
                        ubicumque eidem cenobio diffinivit ad habendum. Quorum peticionibus tota
                        devocione faventes, id fieri anuimus, hoc nostrum preceptum scribi iubentes,
                        per quod prelibate Berte eundem monasterium confirmamus, quatenus in sua sit
                        potestate et dominio cousque vixerit et ibidem dominatrix et ordinatrix
                        atque rectrix invigilet ac permaneat donec eius fuerit vita. Per quod etiam
                        iam prescripto venerabili loco concedimus hac confirmamus omnes res et
                        possessiones mobiles ac inmobiles, tam per <rs key="#Cartula">cartulas</rs>
                        quamque extra cartulas vel cuiuscumque inscripcionis titulo ad partem ipsius
                        monasterii legibus adquisitas et acquirendas, seu quicquid per regum vel
                        imperatorum antecessorum nostrorum precepta ad eundem sacrum locum collatum;
                        atque <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellulam</rs> quandam que antiquitus
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1508" key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Monasterium</orgName> dicebatur non procul a Placentina urbe sitam,
                        loco qui <placeName ref="#places/14"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Caput Trebiae</placeName> vocatur, in qua <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1503"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >ecclesia apostolorum principis honore</orgName> dicata consistit, cum
                        omnibus inibi inibi pertinentibus, quemadmodum <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/80">Karlomannus</persName> serenissimus <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> antiquitus eandem cellulam cum universis
                        suis appendiciis eidem monasterio <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >proprietario iure</rs> largitus est, prenominato venerabili loco per
                        hoc nostrae regalis auctoritatis preceptum ex integro perdonamus, largimur,
                        confirmamus modisque omnibus corroboramus. <rs key="#Personal_statuses"
                            >Familias quoque utriusque sexus et condicionis</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs> et <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs>
                        earumque appendiciis, cum omnibus <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Houses">casis</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, pascuis, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, salectis, sacionibus, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis
                            aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>,
                        fluminibus, <rs key="#Fisheries">piscacionibus</rs>, ripis, rupinis, <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montibus</rs>, collibus, vallibus ac planiciebus,
                        coltis et incoltis, divisis et indivisis, <rs key="#Markets"
                            >mercacionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Public_exactions">vectigalibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Profits_of_justice">districtionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Royal_slave"
                            >servis et ancillis</rs>, <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldiis et
                            aldianis</rs> et omnibus que dici aut nominari possunt ad eundem
                        monasterium iuste et legaliter respicientibus in integrum confirmamus, ita
                        videlicet, ut prelibata abbatissa Berta, quousque vixerit, hac nostra
                        auctoritate roborata de prescriptis rebus eidem monasterio pertinentibus tam
                        per preceptorum paginam, ut diximus, quamque aliarum instrumenta cartarum et
                        adquisitis et adquirendis potestative faciat, omnium magnarum parvarumque
                        personarum molestacione remota. Si quis vero hanc nostram auctoritatem
                        violare temtaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">CL libras auri optimi</rs> componere
                        cogatur, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem camere nostrae</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem sepe fate Berte
                            abbatissae</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur diligenciusque ab omnibus
                        opservetur, manu propria roborantes de anulo nostro iussimus insigniri.
                        Signum (MF) domni Hugonis piissimi regis. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name
                                ref="Sigefredus">Sigefredus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellairus</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/1500">Beati</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. (SR) (SI) data anno
                        dominice incarnacionis DCCCCXXVI, III non. Sep., indiccione XV, anno vero
                        domni Hugonis I. Actum <placeName ref="#places/65">Papia</placeName>. In
                        Christi nomine feliciter, amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>DD U, pp. 6-9, n. II; Falconi, <foreign>Le carte</foreign> I, pp. 124-127, n.
                    50.</p>
            </div>
